    "slug": "landing-vs-homepage",
    "lang": "en",
    "title": "Dedicated Landing Page vs Homepage: Which One Actually Converts Paid Traffic?",
    "description": "Why sending all ad traffic to your homepage often kills conversions — and when you should create a campaign-specific landing page instead.",
    "date": "2026-06-19",
    "tags": [
      "conversion",
      "landing-page",
      "ads"
    ],
    "html": "<p>Many businesses direct every ad campaign (Meta Ads, Google Ads, or promotions) straight to their homepage. Traffic increases, but WhatsApp conversations and actual conversions often stay flat.</p>\n<p>The homepage is important, but it is rarely the best place to turn paid visitors into leads.</p>\n<h2>Why the homepage usually fails for paid traffic</h2>\n<p>A homepage is built to serve <strong>everyone</strong>. It needs to introduce multiple services, showcase portfolio, display testimonials, and provide full navigation. This creates several problems:</p>\n<ul><li>The ad message does not match the page content (message mismatch)</li><li>Visitors are unsure which action to take</li><li>Too many competing CTAs</li><li>Slower load time because of heavy content</li></ul>\n<p>A dedicated landing page, on the other hand, has <strong>one single goal</strong>: get the visitor to perform one primary action (usually starting a WhatsApp chat).</p>\n<h2>When you should create a dedicated landing page</h2>\n<p>Build a separate landing page when:</p>\n<ul><li>You are running paid advertising (Meta, Google, TikTok Ads)</li><li>The campaign promotes a specific offer (discount, event, limited package)</li><li>You have different audience segments (e.g., acne consultation vs general skin check)</li><li>You want to test messaging or design quickly</li></ul>\n<p>Real examples we have delivered: - <a href=\"/portfolio/klinik\">Specialist skin clinic</a> uses a dedicated landing page for “acne consultation” ads — not the main clinic homepage. - <a href=\"/portfolio/properti\">Premium residential property</a> has separate landing pages for each unit type being advertised.</p>\n<h2>Key differences</h2>\n<p>| Aspect             | Homepage                              | Dedicated Landing Page                     | |--------------------|---------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------| | Goal               | Introduce the brand broadly           | Convert one traffic source into leads      | | CTA                | Multiple options                      | One primary button (usually WhatsApp)      | | Messaging          | General                               | Matches the exact ad that was clicked      | | Load speed         | Slower                                | Faster                                     | | Tracking           | Hard to measure per campaign          | Easy to measure (one page = one campaign)  |</p>\n<h2>Quick checklist: do you need a new landing page?</h2>\n<ul class=\"blog-checklist\"><li>Ads are running but conversion is low</li><li>Different traffic sources are sent to the same page</li><li>Homepage has more than two primary CTAs</li><li>Homepage takes more than 3 seconds to load on mobile</li><li>Difficult to measure ROI per campaign</li></ul>\n<p>If three or more boxes are checked, you likely need a dedicated landing page.</p>\n<h2>Next step</h2>\n<p>If you want to improve ad performance, we can help with:</p>\n<ul><li>30-minute audit of your current homepage vs campaign needs</li><li>Structure and copy for a new landing page</li><li>Mobile-first page with one strong CTA</li></ul>\n<p><a href=\"/kontak\">Start a conversation on WhatsApp</a> or explore our work on the <a href=\"/layanan\">Services</a> and <a href=\"/portfolio\">Portfolio</a> pages.</p>\n<p>This article is based on patterns we have applied across more than 20 ad + landing page projects between 2025 and 2026.</p>",
